<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-03T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-03T20:00:00-05:00" n="236" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d236">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">862K.6377/7–347: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Political Adviser in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-03T21:00:00-04:00">July 3,
                                    1947—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>255. Reurtel 175 June 29.<note n="15" xml:id="d236fn15">See footnote 9,
                                    <ref target="#pg_243">p. 243</ref>.</note> Reference Angaur
                            project SecState at July 2 press conference made fol statement:</p>
                        <p>[Here follows quotation of text printed in Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, July 13, 1947, page 101.]</p>
                        <pb facs="0262" n="248" xml:id="pg_248"/>
                        <p>Reference Antarctic whaling expedition Dept has consistently supported
                                <gloss target="#t_SCAP1">SCAP</gloss>’s position in conversations
                            with Ambassadors and other officials interested govts and in press
                            conferences.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>